<p>The idea is pretty simple, I would like to create a Google Calendar (or any other google data item) event with a special Latin-9 (ISO-8859-15) character and echo that to the browser.</p>

<p>If I create an event called "Test: Œ, œ, Ÿ, Š, š, Ž, ž", everything is fine on the web site, google accepts it, renders it just fine.  If I then update my outputCalendar() function to</p>

<pre><code>    echo iconv('UTF-8', 'ISO-8859-15', $event-&gt;title-&gt;text)
</code></pre>

<p>then I get the following event title:</p>

<pre><code> "Test: ¼, ½, ¾, ¦, ¨, ´, "
